ğŸ“Œ C programming mein variables ek memory location hote hai jahan data ko store karna aur access karna adhikmatra hota hai. Variables ko define karne ke liye, aap unke type aur name define karte hai. C programming mein variables ke kuchh basic types hai:

ğŸ“ 1. int (integer): Integer variables ek whole number hote hai, jo -32768 se 32767 tak values store kar sakte hai.

int age;
age = 25;

ğŸ“ 2. float (floating-point number): Floating-point variables decimal values store karte hai.

float price;
price = 4.99;

ğŸ“ 3. double (double-precision floating-point number): Double variables ek floating-point number hote hai, lekin unke accuracy aur range ek bar hi zyada hota hai.

double pi;
pi = 3.141592653589793;

ğŸ“ 4. char (character): Character variables ek single character ko store karte hai.

char letter;
letter = 'A';

ğŸ“ 5. void (no type): Void variables ek special type hai jise function ke return type ke roop mein use kiya jata hai.

void function_name();

ğŸ“Œ C programming mein variables ko define karne ke liye, aap unke type aur name define karte hai, aur agar aapko unki initial value bhi define karni hai, toh aap unhe assign kar sakte hai.

#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
   int age = 25;
   float price = 4.99;
   double pi = 3.141592653589793;
   char letter = 'A';

   printf("age = %d\n", age);
   printf("price = %f\n", price);
   printf("pi = %lf\n", pi);
   printf("letter = %c\n", letter);

   return 0;
}

ğŸ“Œ C programming mein variables ko scope ke anuroop define kar sakte hai. Variables ke scope ek specific area hai jahan unki values access ki ja sakti hai. C programming mein variables ke do scope hai:

ğŸ“ 1: Global variables: Global variables ek program ke kisi bhi part mein access ki ja sakte hai.

#include <stdio.h>

// Global variable definition
int global_var = 10;

int main() {
   // Global variable access
   printf("global_var = %d\n", global_var);

   return 0;
}

ğŸ“ 2: Local variables: Local variables ek function ke andar define hote hai aur unhe sirf unke andar access ki ja sakti hai.

#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
   // Local variable definition
   int local_var = 20;

   // Local variable access
   printf("local_var = %d\n", local_var);

   return 0;
}

ğŸ“Œ C programming mein variables ko scope ke anuroop define karne se, variables ke values function ke andar reuse ho jaati hai, aur program ke performance aur memory management mein fayda hota hai.




